The National Transport and Safety Authority, NTSA has asked motorists to exercise extra caution while driving on the roads following the heavy flooding caused by the ongoing heavy rains and avoid flooded sections to avert any calamities. On its part the Kenya National Highways Authority issued an emergency number and urged Kenyans to report any emergency situations even as the Mai -Mahiu -Narok road was re-opened to motor traffic after being cut-off by floods at Suswa area on Wednesday morning. 